    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I enjoyed reading ''The Panorama of Denali,'' by Eric Asimov (Family Vacations, June 6). It revived fond memories of my vacation in Alaska five years ago. The vast area and incredible beauty are difficult to appreciate without being there.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: I enjoyed reading ''The Panorama of Denali,'' by Eric Asimov (Family Vacations, June 6). It revived fond memories of my vacation in Alaska five years ago. The vast area and incredible beauty are difficult to appreciate without being there.</p>
        <p>For those visitors with time to spare, I would suggest traveling on the Alaska railroad. With Anchorage as our hub, we used the railroad to journey to Talkeetna and Denali, as well as to coastal cities for glacier- and whale-watching by boat. The slower-moving train wends its way through spectacular mountain passes and provides a different perspective than the highway. We visitors from the lower 48 loved it.</p>
        <p>MARK L. AARON  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
